C1:
Welcome to this study!



Your participation is expected to last for about 17 minutes. Please read the following general participation information before starting the survey.



Study Description:

The purpose of this research study is to examine perceptions of eyewitnesses' memories and statements. You will be asked to watch a video and answer questions regarding the video. 



Risks and Benefits:

No risks or discomforts are expected. You will not directly benefit from your participation in this research study. This study may provide valuable information about how people perceive eyewitnesses' memory and statements.



Confidentiality:

Safeguards are taken to maintain the confidentiality of your data. To ensure confidentiality, the project will not collect any information that directly or indirectly personally identifies any research participant (e.g. participant name or IP address). That is, data will be fully anonymized. The anonymous data will be posted online and will be analyzed and reported as statistics only (i.e. aggregated with other participants’ answers). All data will be made publicly available on the Open Science Framework website (osf.io).



If you have any questions or concerns, you can contact Naiara Castello (gusferrena@student.gu.se) or Karl Ask (karl.ask@psy.gu.se).
